{
  "word": "ἄποινα",
  "short": "ransom",
  "medium": "ransom, compensation",
  "syn":"λύτρα",
  "mnemonic_cog":"penalty",
  "cog":"ποινή, penalty; possibly τίνω, τίω, τιμή, τιμάω",
  "etym":"PIE kwoy, punishment, vengeance. Before o, kw changes regularly to p. Kwoy may in turn come from kwey, to observe, honor, which gave rise to τίω et al. The ν comes from neh2, cognate with english -en. Thus ἄποινα = vengeance-ment."
